The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 RAK Ceramics to invest Rs 150 cr

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 

 Khater Massaad (right), founder member and CEO of RAK Ceramics, UAE, with Sunil Malesha, general manager of RAK Ceramics (India), in Mumbai on Wednesday. (Fotocorp)

 Mumbai, Aug. 23: RAK Ceramics, a UAE-based ceramic company, is planning to invest close to Rs 150 crore in setting up its second plant at Gujarat in a drive to expand its presence in India. The company already has a unit at Kakinada, Andhra Pradesh. It is in the process of expanding its dealer network to over 400 and establish 50 exclusive showrooms across the country.

 The $400-million conglomerate, which has manufacturing presence in countries such as China, Iran, Sudan, UAE and Bangladesh, now has the largest vitrified tile manufacturing plant in Andhra Pradesh with an installed capacity of 20,000 sq metres of vitrified tiles per day.

 Khater Massaad, founder member and CEO of RAK Ceramics, said here that while the company has already invested Rs 250 crore, the idea was to invest an additional amount of Rs 70 crore in this fiscal to increase the production capacity at the companys Kakinada plant to 30,000 sq metres per day. 

 The unit, which is expected to come up in Gujarat within the next two years, will involve an investment of up to Rs 150 crore. Sunil Malesha, general manager of RAK Ceramics (India) Pvt Ltd, said, There is a huge growth potential in the Indian market. 




